@NODE "SUP_AMINFO" "AttrMan.guide/SUP_AMINFO"
@TITLE "AttrMan - Am_Info"

   AM_Info
   ~~~~~~~
   AM_Info shows information about the running AttrMan.

   AM_Info has an output somewhat similar like this:

   8> AM_Info
   @{B}AM_Info 1.0/36.0@{UB} ©1996 @{FG Fill}Jeroen Massar@{FG Text}
   This system is using : AttrMan 1.0/36.1 (28.07.96) by Jeroen Massar
                          Global AttrStart: 0x80000000, ChunkSize: 32
   The following 2 users are currently using AttrMan:
   +------+--------------------------------+------------+------------+
   |  No  |              Name              |   Start    |    Size    |
   +------+--------------------------------+------------+------------+
   |    1 | group.class                    | 0x80000000 |        100 |
   |    2 | utilitypatcher                 | 0x80000064 |         12 |
   +------+--------------------------------+------------+------------+

   The first line shows info about AM_Info itself.
   The second line shows the release,version,date and the name of the coder
   of the running copy of AttrMan.
   The third line shows the number of users and the chunksize.
   The following lines show a table containing the name,startvalue and size
   of the area allocated. When AM_Info complains that it couldn't find
   AttrMan simply run it by typing c:AttrMan (that is if you installed it there).

@ENDNODE

